Ad Text:
Senior Business Analyst - Telco

12-Month Contract | $800-$1,000/day | Melbourne CBD (Hybrid)

About the Organisation

Talenza is partnering with a leading telecommunications provider recognised for driving large-scale digital, network, and customer transformation. With millions of customers nationwide and a strong investment in future-focused technology, this organisation offers an exciting opportunity for a Senior BA to join a high-performing delivery environment.

About the Role

As a Senior Business Analyst, you'll play a critical role in shaping, defining, and supporting delivery across major telco initiatives. Working closely with product, technology, networks, engineering, and operations teams, you'll lead detailed analysis, requirements definition, process mapping, and solution alignment across complex workstreams.

You'll be the bridge between the business and delivery teams, ensuring clarity, structure, and traceability throughout the project lifecycle.

Key Responsibilities

Lead requirements gathering, documentation, and validation across multiple telco projects

Facilitate workshops with business, product, engineering, and network stakeholders

Translate business problems into clear, actionable user stories, process flows, and functional documentation

Analyse complex telco processes across billing, OSS/BSS, CRM, networks, or customer experience

Map current vs future-state processes, identifying impacts, gaps, risks, and dependencies

Partner with Solution Architects and SMEs to ensure technical alignment

Support UAT planning, execution, and defect triage

Manage stakeholder expectations and ensure consistent communication

Contribute to governance, reporting, and artefact quality assurance

Support delivery teams in agile and hybrid project environments

Key Selection Criteria

Strong Senior Business Analyst experience within telecommunications

Deep understanding of telco environments - OSS/BSS, CRM, billing, network, or service delivery

Proven ability to translate complex processes into clear analysis artefacts

Significant experience running workshops with technical and non-technical stakeholders

Familiarity with agile delivery (user stories, backlogs, acceptance criteria)

Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with strong attention to detail

Ability to operate in fast-paced, large enterprise transformation environments

As a Director – Data & AI Strategy, you will lead the growth, development, and implementation of Data & AI Strategy services across Publicis Sapient in Australia. This includes identifying new opportunities, shaping value propositions, and fostering organic growth in existing relationships. You will leverage your expertise in data and AI to drive transformative strategies while working closely with Publicis Sapient’s digital transformation technology teams.

Key Responsibilities:

Identify and Create Opportunities: Build strategic relationships with senior clients to identify opportunities that harness data and AI strategy for transformative impact.
Shape and Nurture AI-Driven Data Strategies: Originate, shape, and nurture data and AI strategy opportunities, guiding them from inception through to full implementation.
Develop Market-Leading Propositions: Create forward-thinking data and AI strategy propositions that address client needs and emerging industry trends.
Drive New Business & Organic Growth: Source and close new business development opportunities and identify areas for organic growth within existing client accounts, leveraging AI and data strategies.
Lead High-Profile Engagements: Spearhead high-profile data and AI strategy engagements, delivering innovative solutions and measurable impact.
Expand Programs of Delivery: Scale data and AI strategy projects into larger, multi-disciplinary programs of delivery, fostering end-to-end transformation.
Contribute to Global Data & AI Policies: Play a key role in developing and implementing global policies and standards for data and AI strategies.
Cultivate a Talented Team: Mentor and develop talent within the data and AI strategy team, fostering a culture of innovation and continuous improvement.
Build Thought Leadership & Team Growth: Actively contribute to the growth of the data and AI strategy team by supporting recruitment, establishing best practices, and providing thought leadership in the industry.

Qualifications

Deep Data & AI Domain Expertise: Over 10 years of experience in roles such as data engineering, data science, AI strategy, or data analytics, with an emphasis on integrating AI into business solutions.
Advanced Knowledge in Key Areas: Proven expertise in at least one of the following: data engineering (data platforms, cloud environments), data science (machine learning & AI deployment, data product development), or data analytics (instrumentation, reporting, optimization, experimentation & MarTech).
AI Strategy Vision: Ability to translate complex data and AI topics into understandable, actionable insights for senior stakeholders, and align these insights with business strategies.
Proven Transformation Delivery: Track record of delivering complex data and AI-driven transformation programs with demonstrable impact on business outcomes.
Senior Stakeholder Management: Skilled at building and sustaining relationships with senior clients, delivering impactful and strategic work.
Leadership & Team Development: Demonstrated experience in growing team capability, developing talent, and managing the financial performance of team-delivered projects.
Agile and Tech-Savvy: Strong appreciation for Agile ways of working, modern technology tools, engineering practices, and AI methodologies.
Strong Communication & Consulting Skills: Excellent written, verbal, numerical, and presentation skills, with experience consulting to C-level clients.
Analytical & Innovative Mindset: Creative, curious, deeply analytical, and passionate about data and AI-driven problem-solving.
Openness to Travel: Willingness to travel and work on client sites to deliver exceptional, high-impact services

Nice-to-Have:

Deep experience in two or more of the following industries: Banking, Insurance, Wealth, Retail, Public Sector.
Experience in both established and challenger professional services firms, with an entrepreneurial and growth mindset.

Senior Associate Data Engineering L2


Role Summary:

As a Senior Associate, Data Engineering at Publicis Sapient, you will architect and implement innovative solutions that drive digital transformation. Your expertise will shape large-scale data ingestion, processing, storage, and analytics in mostly cloud environments. You will design and implement data models, data storage, performance optimisation, security, DevOps, and test automation solutions.

This role requires a hands-on approach, working collaboratively with other Data specialists in a culture that values continuous learning and knowledge sharing.

Key Responsibilities:

Work closely with our clients, designing solutions for data platforms, with a focus on ETL, ELT, ALT, lambda, and kappa architectures.
Build prototypes and solutions for cloud, on-prem, hybrid, and edge-based data platforms.
Create and maintain infrastructure-as-code for cloud, on-prem, and hybrid environments using tools such as Terraform, CloudFormation, Azure Resource Manager, Helm, and Google Cloud Deployment Manager.

Must-Have:

Deep understanding of modern Data Architecture and its application to business transformation.
Expertise in cloud-native architectures, with practical experience in hyperscaler platforms.
Experience designing, building, and optimising scalable data pipelines and distributed systems in Snowflake and/or Databricks.
Expertise in Python and SQL, with deep knowledge of performance tuning, sharding, partitioning, and indexing.
Understanding of database technologies, including relational, NoSQL, and cloud-native storage solutions.
Experience in CI/CD, automated testing, and cloud infrastructure-as-code.
Excellent written, verbal, numerical, and presentation skills.

Nice-to-Have:

Experience in two or more of the following industries: Banking, Insurance, Wealth, Retail, Public Sector.
Experience in both established and challenger professional services firms, with an entrepreneurial and growth mindset.

Job Title: Manager - Workforce Services, Systems & Analytics, Education
Category:
Strategy & Planning (Consulting & Strategy)
Government - State (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
The role provides strategic direction and system-wide leadership for workforce planning, ensuring the Department's long-term workforce needs are understood, modelled, and clearly communicated. It enables regions and schools to anticipate local requirements and take proactive action to meet future demand. The position strengthens workforce planning maturity by integrating predictive insights, regional collaboration, and system capability uplift.

About the Department of Education:

Working for the Queensland Department of Education means joining an organisation that values its people and promotes leadership and innovation. Be part of an environment that respects professionalism and diversity,  offers training and development opportunities and embraces flexible careers and work-life balance. Find out more about working with us.

About the Work Environment and Team

The role sits within Workforce Analytics and Reporting, a unit that supports the Department's vision for equity and excellence by providing clear workforce insights that guide strategic decision making. The team values accuracy, clarity, and collaboration, and operates across both state and regional contexts.

The work is analytical, forward-looking, and system-focused, with strong links to senior leaders across the Department. The team culture supports shared problem solving, capability uplift, and a focus on practical and consistent approaches to workforce planning.

The environment is one where data, modelling, and system priorities come together to guide the long-term planning needed to support schools and regions across Queensland. It is a collaborative setting that values clear thinking, proactive planning, and the effective communication of complex information.

Why this Role?

Lead the operation and ongoing refinement of the Department's Teacher Supply and Demand Model in Power BI, ensuring insights are accurate, timely, and accessible for statewide, regional, and school workforce planning.
Integrate demographic, enrolment, and workforce data into clear planning outputs, and apply risk assessment and sensitivity analysis to support long-term workforce strategies.
Represent the Department in state and national workforce planning forums and contribute to data-sharing, policy discussions, and sector-wide planning initiatives.
Build capability across regional HR teams to interpret and apply workforce forecasts, and support the consistent adoption of workforce planning practices.
Provide expert advice on workforce supply, retention, mobility, and pipeline strategies, including targeted approaches for hard-to-fill teaching areas.
Develop and maintain workforce planning frameworks, tools, and resources that strengthen planning maturity and support alignment between school, regional, and system planning.
Present complex modelling and analysis in clear, meaningful ways that inform executive decision making and proactive planning for emerging workforce risks.

Skills and Experience

In-depth experience in workforce planning, workforce analytics, or a related strategic HR or planning field.
Demonstrated capability in managing complex modelling or forecasting tools (ideally Power BI) and using integrated datasets to produce actionable insights.
High-level analytical skills, including risk assessment, scenario modelling, and interpreting trends to support long-term workforce decisions.
Experience providing authoritative advice to senior leaders on workforce issues such as supply, retention, mobility, and pipeline needs.
Proven ability to lead, coach, or uplift capability within teams responsible for planning or analysis.
Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to present complex data in clear and practical ways for non-technical audiences.
Experience working in environments that require sound judgement, governance, and an understanding of organisational priorities.

Interested? To Apply: 

Attach a brief resume including contact details for 2 referees (referees should have an understanding of your relevant work history)
Attach a 1-page written statement about how your achievements and capabilities meet the requirements of the role

We welcome all applicants to share any support needed to ensure our recruitment process is inclusive.

Applications remain current for 12 months from the closing date and may be considered for appointment to identical or similar vacancies within the Department.

Applications from recruitment agencies will not be accepted.
